2000_August 23 

How can one say that this is an honest and open-minded approach to Joan of
Arc's character? The reason for her &quot;revenge&quot; is not historically accurate.
Joan is portrayed as a raving maniac who eventually makes the viewer wonder
why she would ever be canonized a saint. This movie is in short a huge time
waster. The Ingrid Bergman version is the movie to see if one wishes get a
more realistic glimpse of Joan's true character.
